text:
Ming Ji Wanton Mee has been my constant place to get my breakfast / lunch.

$4 for a basic wanton noddle set. Higher price for fancier one but all still under $10 per pax 4sure.

Great wanton mee. Lovely soup, hardworking folks. Give it a try. Will not disappoint. Just maybe differed type of wanton style from you had personally.

I hope they keep going! Positive employees.

Food is not bad. Noodles cooked al dente with bite, not too mushy.

Tried the signature to see what stands out, individually all ok, can eat lah. Price is reasonable.

The wanton mee taste like bak Chor Mee style. I didnâ€™t like it

Noodles are ok and abit spicy

Donâ€™t recommend

Very normal wanton noodles with very old school, dry, lean, red coloured char siew n not the charred type of char siew with proportionate of fats n lean meats but comes with a few pieces of crispy lards.
Noodles tossed in tasteless sauce. Wanton soup is just weird. Char siew also tough. ðŸ˜­
